Don Syme wrote:
> 
> Shouldn't "[| [] |]" count as a value??
> 
> # let x = [| [] |];;
> val x : '_a list array = [|[]|]
> # let x = [];;
> val x : 'a list = []
> # let x = [| |];;
> val x : 'a array = [||]

No, because you can assign to arrays:

# let x = [| [] |];;
val x : '_a list array = [|[]|]
# x.(0) <- [1];;
- : unit = ()
# x;;
- : int list array = [|[1]|]

You cannot assign anything to the empty array [| |], however.

Regards,

	- Andreas

